1 truant from school;
2 (5) The officer has reasonable grounds to believe the juvenile is
3 immune from prosecution for prostitution under subsection (5) of section
4 28-801;
5 (6) A juvenile is seriously endangered in his or her surroundings
6 and immediate removal appears to be necessary for the juvenile's
7 protection;
8 (7) A juvenile has committed an act or engaged in behavior described
9 in subdivision (1), (2), (3)(b), or (4) of section 43-247 and such
10 juvenile was under eleven years of age at the time of such act or
11 behavior, and the officer has reasonable cause to believe such juvenile
