1 county attorney of the county where probation was imposed and the
2 juvenile's attorney of record and submit a written report describing the
3 risk of harm to lives or property or of fleeing the jurisdiction which
4 precipitated the need for such detention or deprivation of liberty and of
5 any violation of probation. If there is no attorney of record for the
6 juvenile, the office shall notify the court and counsel for the juvenile
7 shall be appointed. After prompt consideration of the written report, the
8 county attorney shall:
9 (a) Order the release of the juvenile from confinement or
